more north of the river a mauritanian will say the frontier was 
south of it 
and if it hadnt been for the french an official in 
nouakchott said the moroccans would have controlled the whole 
territory 
mauritanian officials say the river is the border north of the 
river is mauritania they say and if mauritanians want to farm the 
land they have every right to do so 
all mauritanian land is in the public domain and the government 
will give it to any mauritanian who wants to develop it 
farmers from senegal say moors dont want to get their hands 
dirty by farming that they are forming large agricultural 
companies and becoming agribusinessmen profiting from land 
developed by senegalese 
dams built near the mouth of the senegal river at diama and at 
manantali in mali have brought vast changes no longer must 
farmers hope for an annual flood to soak the land the dams 
guarantee a flood each year 
irrigation is possible farther back from the river making more 
land arable and enticing investors the prospects are of great 
interest to mauritania which is 99 percent desert 
the white mauritanians want to take the land from the 
toucouleurs said an agricultural technician who has worked in 
