pakistan will give aids tests to all 
foreigners living in pakistan and to citizens who have lived 
abroad it was reported saturday 
health minister amir haider kazmi disclosed the new policy 
friday newspapers reported he was quoted as saying the testing 
would begin some time after june 
finland will lend pakistan 17 million to buy aids testing 
equipment for 440 health facilities in major cities kazmi said 
all foreigners living here for six months or more as well as 
pakistanis who have recently lived abroad will be required to 
undergo the test he said he did not give further details 
there is no known cure for aids or acquired immune deficiency 
syndrome which attacks the bodys immune system 
according to kazmi 29 aids cases have been reported in this 
country of 107 million six are pakistanis and the rest foreigners 
mainly from africa he said three aids victims have died he said 
