the government is in place i am making this fact known to our 
people and the whole world 
that same day nagy took refuge in the yugoslav embassy weeks 
later he and his associates were kidnapped by the soviets and held 
in romania until brought back to hungary and executed in june 
1958 
recently hungarys revolt against stalinism and soviet rule and 
nagys role as its leader have been examined with more sympathy 
politburo reformer imre pozsgay declared in january that the revolt 
was a popular uprising and communist authorities opened up the 
archives to historians 
on june 16 the anniversary of his execution thousands of 
hungarians are expected to attend the reburial of nagy and his 
associates in a corner of a budapest cemetery where the bodies have 
lain in unmarked graves since 1958 
the broadcast saturday of nagys speech came in a morning 
broadcast on radio kossuth scholar maria ormos had just given a 
summary of a discussion held friday by historians they called for 
opening the archives on the 195358 period and they blamed soviet 
interference for the failure of the revolt and for the failure of a 
1953 attempt at reform 
after the interview the radio mentioned several new 
publications on the 1956 period including a compilation of the 
text of radio broadcasts by nagy and his supporters during the 
shortlived 1956 revolt the collection is edited by janos kenedi 
a wellknown member of hungarys democratic opposition 
kenedi told radio kossuth the material was collected by radio 
free europe and published abroad but would now appear for the first 
time in hungary 
the radio then closed out the broadcast with the nagy speech 
which has been broadcast on the usfunded munichbased rfe every 
nov 4 for years in memory of the end of the 1956 revolt 
the sweeping revision of hungarian history began after the 
ouster in may of janos kadar as communist party chief kadar took 
over as hungarian leader after the revolt was crushed his role in 
the uprising has never been clear and he has refused to give a 
public accounting of those days 
kadar 76 is said to be too ill to carry out official duties as 
honorary chairman of the party a post created when he was replaced 
as party chief last year by karoly grosz 
unconfirmed reports say that kadar is unhappy about the recent 
discussion of 1956 and the gradual rehabilitation of nagy a new 
biography of nagy is selling briskly and his picture appears on 
lapel pins sold in budapest kiosks 
