set up checkpoints late friday to control access into the former 
panama canal zone where many us military personnel live 
us personnel have had no problems leaving the former zone 
area despite the panamanian checkpoints the southern command 
official said speaking on condition of anonymity 
the command citing possible disturbances planned to increase 
security on saturday it previously had urged the estimated 12000 
american troops stationed in panama to go into the capital only on 
essential business 
the canal zone once was controlled by the united states but was 
among the areas that reverted to panamanian control under the 
panama canal treaties of 1977 
under the treaties full control of the canal is to be turned 
over to panama in 1999 but the tense relations between noriega and 
washington have complicated that treaty 
the bush administration saying election fraud likely will 
