the eight parties in the progovernment national liberation 
coalition contend that the opposition and the united states plan to 
delay or cancel handing over the canal 
opposition presidential candidate guillermo endara has said he 
will fire noriega if the general wont retire although noriega has 
installed and deposed presidents at will since he took control of 
the armed forces in 1983 
endara is running for the fiveyear term under the banner of the 
democratic opposition alliance a threeparty coalition 
the winner takes office sept 1 
about 12 million of panamas 22 residents are registered to 
vote polls are open from 7 am 8 am edt to 5 pm the 
government has promised results within 24 hours after polls close 
in the last election in 1984 nicolas ardito barletta was 
